article.headline: Wagner 64, St. Francis, NY 59
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Durrell Vinson had 24 points and 14 rebounds to lead Wagner to a 64-59 victory over St. Francis, N.Y. on Saturday. Mark Porter added 14 points for the Seahawks (6-3, 1-0 Northeast Conference), while Jamal Smith had 12. Marcus Williams led the visiting Terriers (3-6, 0-2) with 20 points, while Robert Hines had 15 and Jamal Womack 14. The Seahawks led 36-21 at halftime and Vinson's jumper with 11:10 to play made it 56-35. Williams then had eight points in the Terriers' 17-2 run that got them within 58-52 on a 3-pointer by Hines with 4:03 left. St. Francis closed within 60-59 on a layup by Williams with 1:23 to go but Vinson went 4-for-4 from the free throw line the rest of the way.
